external_knowledge:
- 'Enthusiastic applause' refers to ratings greater than 7;
- 'Tepid claps' refers to ratings less than 4;
- 'Stand out among the crowd' means the movie has more high ratings than low ratings;
- 'Over 10 reviews' indicates the movie has been rated more than 10 times.

- 'stellar ratings' refers to high average ratings from user ratings;
- 'captivating watch times' refers to the total duration users have spent watching the movie;
- 'abundant tags' refers to the number of tags associated with the movie;
- 'frequent searches' refers to the number of times the movie title appears in user search queries.

- "Shining stars" refers to movies that are highly rated, popular in watchlists, or frequently discussed by moderators;
- "User-generated ratings" are ratings provided by regular users;
- "Watchlist popularity" is the frequency with which a movie appears in user watchlists;
- "Moderator feedback" is feedback provided by users with a 'moderator' role.

sql:
SELECT user_id, COUNT(search_id) AS search_count
FROM user_searches
GROUP BY user_id;

external_knowledge:
- A "highly rated" movie is one with a user rating greater than 6;
- A "positively reviewed" movie is one with a feedback rating greater than 6;
- "Actually watched" means the movie has a non-null `watched_at` timestamp.

- "adorned with more than five tags" refers to movies that have more than 5 tags associated with them;
- "appearing in over five watchlists" refers to movies that are added to more than 5 user watchlists;
- "belonging to more than five genres" refers to movies that are classified under more than 5 genres;
- "stellar reputation" refers to movies that either have no average user rating or an average user rating greater than 5.

- "Top 3 movies" refers to the movies with the highest average ratings within their respective genres;
- "Average rating" is calculated from user ratings;
- "Genres" are categories that classify movies.

- "User ratings" refer to the numerical scores given by users to movies, typically on a scale from 1 to 10;
- "Viewing habits" refer to the patterns of how users watch movies, including the number of unique viewers and the average duration watched;
- "Tag diversity" refers to the variety of descriptive tags associated with movies, which can be user-generated or moderator-approved;
- "Genre representation" refers to the classification of movies into different genres, such as action, drama, comedy, etc.;
- "Action movies" are those classified under the action genre;
- "Release year" is the year in which the movie was first made available to the public.

- "Popular" is determined by a score that combines watchlist frequency, average rating, feedback, and tags;
- The score is calculated as: (watchlist frequency * watchlist frequency) + (watchlist frequency * average rating) + (watchlist frequency * feedback count) + (watchlist frequency * tag count);
- The movie with the highest score is considered the most popular.

- 'Average rating' is calculated by averaging the ratings given by users for each movie;
- 'Watchlist count' is the number of times a movie appears in user watchlists;
- 'Tag count' is the number of user-generated tags associated with each movie;
- 'Genre' is the category of the movie, such as action, drama, etc.;
- 'Usernames' refer to the usernames of users who have added the movies to their watchlists.

- "Cinephiles" are enthusiasts of cinema or movies;
- "Delved into more than one cinematic journey" means watched at least 2 movies;
- "Extent of their exploration" includes the total number of movies watched, the average rating given, and the total duration of movies watched;
- "Movie-watching odyssey" refers to the total duration of all movies watched by each user.

- "blossomed in the hearts of users" refers to movies that have been positively received by users;
- "watched halfway through" means the user has watched at least 50% of the movie;
- "rated more than a 5-star experience" indicates a rating higher than 5.

- "tagged more than once" means the movie has more than one tag associated with it;
- "watched" means the movie has been watched by at least one user;
- "added to watchlists" means the movie is part of at least one user's watchlist.

- 'Turn of the millennium' refers to the year 2000;
- 'Captured the hearts of many' refers to movies appearing on more than 10 user watchlists;
- 'Stellar average user rating' refers to an average rating greater than 5.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(tag_id) AS total_user_generated_tags
FROM user_tags
WHERE tag_source = 'user-generated';

SELECT user_id, COUNT(movie_id) AS number_of_movies_viewed
FROM user_views
GROUP BY user_id;

SELECT user_id, watchlist_name
FROM user_watchlists
WHERE watchlist_name = 'To Watch';

SELECT user_id, watchlist_name
FROM user_watchlists
ORDER BY user_id DESC;

SELECT COUNT(rating) 
FROM user_ratings
WHERE rating > (SELECT AVG(rating) FROM user_ratings);
